{# 
    Quotation (<q>)
    ===========================================================================
    Defines a short inline quotation.

    Variables:
    - `quote_text`: The text to be displayed as a quotation. Defaults to "Quoted text".
    - `quote_cite`: The URL of the source of the quote. Defaults to "#".

    Notes:
    - The `| e` filter is used to escape any special characters in the variables to prevent XSS attacks.
    - The `cite` attribute is optional and provides the source of the quotation.

    Links:
    - https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/q
    - https://www.w3schools.com/tags/tag_q.asp

#}

<q cite="{{ quote_cite | default('#') | e }}">
    {{ quote_text | default('Quoted text') | e }}
</q>
